      "id": "T-1",
      "type": "story",
      "title": "unify show-tree rendering across ticket and decision surfaces",
      "description": "Audit which surfaces build a ticket/decision join-tree (ancestors, decisions, blockers, children) and route them all through buildShowTree (introduced in v1.4.5 in internal/cli/ticket.go). Currently used by ticket show, ticket refine next, ticket refine write. Plan whatsnext / plan review use the older whatNextResult shape; decisions show may have a parallel pattern. Goal: one canonical helper, identical JSON output where the data overlaps, single place to tweak rendering.",
      "status": "ready",
      "priority": "medium",
      "assigned_to": "claude",
      "created_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:05",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:09"
    },
    {
      "id": "T-2",
      "type": "task",
      "parent_id": "T-1",
      "title": "route plan whatsnext and plan review through buildShowTree",
      "description": "Replace whatNextResult in internal/cli/plan.go with the ticketShowTree shape (or refactor whatNextResult to embed it). enrichTicket already returns the same ancestors/children/decisions data — collapse the two so plan whatsnext, plan review, ticket show, and ticket refine emit identical join-tree JSON for the same ticket. Keep the Message field for the no-actionable-tickets case.",
      "status": "ready",
      "priority": "medium",
      "assigned_to": "claude",
      "created_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:05",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:09"
    },
    {
      "id": "T-3",
      "type": "task",
      "parent_id": "T-1",
      "title": "align decisions show with the join-tree helper pattern",
      "description": "Audit internal/cli/decisions.go (decisions show with --with-refs / --with-tickets) for a parallel ad-hoc tree shape. If found, factor into a buildDecisionTree helper analogous to buildShowTree so decision rendering stays consistent across decisions show, decisions read, and any future surface (e.g. plan status drilldowns).",
      "status": "ready",
      "priority": "medium",
      "assigned_to": "claude",
      "created_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:05",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-06 10:07:09"
    },
    {
      "id": "T-4",
      "type": "bug",
      "title": "pre-commit hook misses bootstrap snapshot when pql-plan.json is untracked",
      "description": "internal/cli/init.go:374 pqlPreCommitHook gates 'git add' on 'git diff --quiet -- .pql/pql-plan.json'. For an untracked file, git diff returns 0 (no diff) so the negation is false and the file is never staged. Result: the first commit after 'pql init' silently fails to commit the planning snapshot. Reproducer: fresh repo, pql init, pql ticket new ..., git commit -m '...' — pql-plan.json stays untracked. Fix: also stage when the file exists but is untracked, e.g. test 'git ls-files --error-unmatch ... 2\u003e/dev/null' or unconditionally 'git add -f .pql/pql-plan.json' if the file exists. Update both the embedded hook script and any tests asserting hook behaviour.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "high",
      "assigned_to": "claude",
      "created_at": "2026-05-06 10:11:03",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-06 10:12:26"
    }
  ],
